comments: Porter Jr. (DEN) contests Alexander-Walker's (MIN) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Conley (MIN) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Porter Jr. (DEN).
Gobert (MIN) brings his hands toward Murray (DEN) and marginal contact occurs as Gobert (MIN) releases away to roll.
Gobert (MIN) firms up in Murray's (DEN) path and marginal side to side contact occurs as Murray contorts his body to go over the pick.
Jokic (DEN) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects it away from Gobert (MIN).
Conley (MIN) initiates contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm, which affects Jokic's SQBR. There are under two minutes left in the game and therefore this is not a transition take foul situation.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) establishes himself in a wide screening position in Alexander-Walker's (MIN) path, but the lower body contact that occurs during the pick is marginal.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) does not make any contact with the ball during Murray's (DEN) pass.
Jokic (DEN) briefly grasps and immediately releases Towns' (MIN) extended arm as marginal contact occurs before Jokic cleanly gathers the ball at the end of the drive.
Towns (MIN) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) and Gordon (DEN) both make clean contact with the ball to block and dislodge the ball from Gobert (MIN) during the shot attempt at the basket.
Gobert (MIN) briefly places a hand on Jokic's (DEN) back as he backs him down in the post and the contact is marginal.
Conley (MIN) and Caldwell-Pope (DEN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off ball.

During the inbound, Towns (MIN) and Jokic (DEN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as they approach the screen. After they disengage, Alexander-Walker (MIN) is retreating and incidental leg to leg contact occurs with Jokic.
Porter Jr. (DEN) firms up in Towns' (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the screen.
Towns (MIN) initiates contact to Jokic's (DEN) front that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Edwards (MIN) during the jump shot attempt. Murray (DEN) avoids contact with Edwards' arm.
After the ball is dislodged, Edwards (MIN) makes incidental contact with the ball during the follow-through from his jump shot attempt.
Brown (DEN) gains full control of the loose ball and gathers on his left foot before taking two legal steps into his shot attempt.

Alexander-Walker (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball and temporarily dislodges it away from Murray (DEN). After Murray regains control, Alexander-Walker's hand slides off the ball and marginal contact occurs with Murray's arm as he makes his intended pass.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Murray's (DEN) arm as he receives the hand-off and starts his dribble.
Jokic (DEN) firms up in Alexander-Walker's (MIN) path and slightly turns his body as marginal side to side contact occurs during the pick.
Gobert (MIN) contests the layup attempt and marginal contact occurs with Jokic's (DEN) arm after the release.
Jokic (DEN) rests his forearm on Edwards' (MIN) side and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) and Murray (DEN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs as the screen is set.
Jokic (DEN) is late to establish himself in Alexander-Walker's (MIN) path, who is a moving defender, and delivers illegal contact during the pick.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Murray's (DEN) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) legally contests Murray's (DEN) layup attempt.
Murray (DEN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Gobert (MIN) receives the pass on his right foot and takes more than two steps before coming to a stop.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) and Murray (DEN) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) attempts to immediately slide his hand off Jokic's (DEN) body when Jokic grasps his arm to briefly hold the marginal contact off-ball.
Alexander-Walker (MIN) is retreating alongside Murray's (DEN) path with a hand resting on his body and marginal contact occurs as Murray releases at the end of the drive.

Murray (DEN) cradles the ball against his body to gather on his left foot and takes one step before coming to a jump stop on two feet for his second step. He is no longer allowed to pivot, which he does before releasing his pass.
Gobert (MIN) quickly slides his hand off Jokic's (DEN) body and marginal contact occurs before he secures the pass.

Gobert (MIN) is retracting his arm from Jokic's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs with Jokic's face/head when he spins into it during the post move.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Gobert (MIN) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) layup attempt.
Conley (MIN) moves alongside Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) path and rests his arm on his side as marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Gobert (MIN) inadvertently steps on Jokic's (DEN) foot as Jokic stops short and incidental contact occurs as they come together during the inbounds play.
Gordon (DEN) commits a take foul on Edwards (MIN).
Porter Jr. (DEN) commits a take foul on Conley (MIN).
Edwards (MIN) makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Braun (DEN) during the jump shot attempt.
